Title: Tempura
Ingredients: Noodles, broth, pork, egg, green onions
Description: Heat a pan over medium heat. Add 2 tablespoons of oil. Sauté 1 chopped onion until golden. Add 2 cloves of minced garlic and cook for 1 minute. Stir in 1 teaspoon of salt, 1/2 teaspoon of pepper, and 1 teaspoon of paprika. Add 1 pound of chicken and cook until browned. Pour in 2 cups of broth and simmer for 20 minutes.

Title: Green Curry
Ingredients: Pasta, tomato sauce, cheese, ground beef, basil
Description: Bring 6 cups of water to a boil. Add 2 cups of pasta and 1 teaspoon of salt. Cook for 10 minutes, then drain. In a saucepan, melt 2 tablespoons of butter, add 1/2 cup of cream, and 1/2 cup of grated cheese. Stir until smooth. Mix with the pasta and serve warm.

Title: Dal Tadka
Ingredients: Egusi seeds, spinach, stockfish, palm oil
Description: Chop 2 potatoes, 1 carrot, and 1 onion. Heat 2 tablespoons of oil in a pot. Sauté the onion for 3 minutes. Add the potatoes and carrots, followed by 4 cups of vegetable broth. Season with 1 teaspoon of salt and 1/2 teaspoon of thyme. Simmer for 20 minutes until tender.

Title: Taco Salad

Title: Egusi Soup
Ingredients: Pasta, tomato sauce, cheese, ground beef, basil
Description: Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C). Grease a baking dish with 1 tablespoon of butter. In a bowl, mix 2 cups of flour, 1 teaspoon of baking powder, and 1/2 teaspoon of salt. Description: Bring 6 cups of water to a boil. Add 2 cups of pasta and 1 teaspoon of salt. Cook for 10 minutes, then drain. In a saucepan, melt 2 tablespoons of butter, add 1/2 cup of cream, and 1/2 cup of grated cheese. Stir until smooth. Mix with the pasta and serve warm.

Title: Tom Yum Soup
Ingredients: Shrimp, flour, eggs, tempura sauce
Description: Boil 4 cups of water in a pot. Add 1 cup of rice and 1/2 teaspoon of salt. Cover and cook on low heat for 15 minutes. Fluff with a fork and serve.

Title: Sweet and Sour Chicken
Ingredients: Flour, butter, sugar, eggs, yeast
Description: Bring 6 cups of water to a boil. Add 2 cups of pasta and 1 teaspoon of salt. Cook for 10 minutes, then drain. In a saucepan, melt 2 tablespoons of butter, add 1/2 cup of cream, and 1/2 cup of grated cheese. Stir until smooth. Mix with the pasta and serve warm.

Title: Ramen
Ingredients: Tomatoes, eggs, onions, bell peppers, spices
Description: Heat 3 tablespoons of oil in a pan. Add 1 sliced bell pepper and 1 diced tomato. Cook for 5 minutes. Add 1 cup of chopped chicken, 1 teaspoon of cumin, and 1/2 teaspoon of chili powder. Stir well and cook for another 10 minutes.

Title: Croissant
Ingredients: Flour, butter, sugar, eggs, yeast
Description: Heat a pan over medium heat. Add 2 tablespoons of oil. Sauté 1 chopped onion until golden. Add 2 cloves of minced garlic and cook for 1 minute. Stir in 1 teaspoon of salt, 1/2 teaspoon of pepper, and 1 teaspoon of paprika. Add 1 pound of chicken and cook until browned. Pour in 2 cups of broth and simmer for 20 minutes.

Title: Sweet and Sour Chicken
Ingredients: Tomatoes, eggs, onions, bell peppers, spices
Description: In a blender, combine 2 bananas, 1 cup of milk, 1/2 teaspoon of cinnamon, and 1 tablespoon of honey. Blend until smooth. Serve chilled.

Description: In a blender, combine 2 bananas, 1 cup of milk, 1/2 teaspoon of cinnamon, and 1 tablespoon of honey. Blend until smooth. Serve chilled.

Title: Pizza Margherita
Ingredients: Ground beef, lettuce, cheese, salsa, tortilla chips
Description: Heat 3 tablespoons of oil in a pan. Add 1 sliced bell pepper and 1 diced tomato. Cook for 5 minutes. Add 1 cup of chopped chicken, 1 teaspoon of cumin, and 1/2 teaspoon of chili powder. Stir well and cook for another 10 minutes.

Title: Ratatouille
Ingredients: Chicken, peanuts, chili peppers, soy sauce
Description: Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C). Grease a baking dish with 1 tablespoon of butter. In a bowl, mix 2 cups of flour, 1 teaspoon of baking powder, and 1/2 teaspoon of salt. In another bowl, whisk 1 cup of milk, 1 egg, and 1/2 cup of sugar. Combine wet and dry ingredients, pour into the baking dish, and bake for 25 minutes.

Title: Lasagna
Ingredients: Egusi seeds, spinach, stockfish, palm oil
Description: Marinate 1 pound of beef with 1 teaspoon of salt, 1/2 teaspoon of black pepper, and 1 tablespoon of soy sauce. Let it sit for 30 minutes. Heat a pan with 2 tablespoons of oil. Sear the beef for 5 minutes on each side. Reduce heat and cook for another 10 minutes, then serve.

Title: Tom Yum Soup
Ingredients: Shrimp, lemongrass, lime leaves, chili, broth
Description: Boil 4 cups of water in a pot. Add 1 cup of rice and 1/2 teaspoon of salt. Cover and cook on low heat for 15 minutes. Fluff with a fork and serve.

Title: Taco Salad
Ingredients: Lentils, garlic, tomatoes, cumin, mustard seeds
Description: Bring 6 cups of water to a boil. Add 2 cups of pasta and 1 teaspoon of salt. Cook for 10 minutes, then drain. In a saucepan, melt 2 tablespoons of butter, add 1/2 cup of cream, and 1/2 cup of grated cheese. Stir until smooth. Mix with the pasta and serve warm.

Title: Kung Pao Chicken
Ingredients: Dough, ground meat, onions, salt, pepper
Description: Heat a pan over medium heat. Add 2 tablespoons of oil. Sauté 1 chopped onion until golden. Add 2 cloves of minced garlic and cook for 1 minute. Stir in 1 teaspoon of salt, 1/2 teaspoon of pepper, and 1 teaspoon of paprika. Add 1 pound of chicken and cook until browned. Pour in 2 cups of broth and simmer for 20 minutes.

Title: Croissant
Ingredients: Shrimp, flour, eggs, tempura sauce
Description: Heat 3 tablespoons of oil in a pan. Add 1 sliced bell pepper and 1 diced tomato. Cook for 5 minutes. Add 1 cup of chopped chicken, 1 teaspoon of cumin, and 1/2 teaspoon of chili powder. Stir well and cook for another 10 minutes.

Title: Pelmeni
Ingredients: Chicken, butter, cream, tomatoes, spices

In another bowl, whisk 1 cup of milk, 1 egg, and 1/2 cup of sugar. Combine wet and dry ingredients, pour into the baking dish, and bake for 25 minutes.

Description: Chop 2 potatoes, 1 carrot, and 1 onion. Heat 2 tablespoons of oil in a pot. Sauté the onion for 3 minutes. Add the potatoes and carrots, followed by 4 cups of vegetable broth. Season with 1 teaspoon of salt and 1/2 teaspoon of thyme. Simmer for 20 minutes until tender.

Title: Egusi Soup
Ingredients: Chickpeas, tahini, lemon, garlic, olive oil
Description: Heat a pan over medium heat. Add 2 tablespoons of oil. Sauté 1 chopped onion until golden. Add 2 cloves of minced garlic and cook for 1 minute. Stir in 1 teaspoon of salt, 1/2 teaspoon of pepper, and 1 teaspoon of paprika. Add 1 pound of chicken and cook until browned. Pour in 2 cups of broth and simmer for 20 minutes.

Title: Borscht
Ingredients: Lentils, garlic, tomatoes, cumin, mustard seeds
Description: Boil 4 cups of water in a pot. Add 1 cup of rice and 1/2 teaspoon of salt. Cover and cook on low heat for 15 minutes. Fluff with a fork and serve.

Title: Ratatouille
Ingredients: Chicken, butter, cream, tomatoes, spices
Description: Heat 3 tablespoons of oil in a pan. Add 1 sliced bell pepper and 1 diced tomato. Cook for 5 minutes. Add 1 cup of chopped chicken, 1 teaspoon of cumin, and 1/2 teaspoon of chili powder. Stir well and cook for another 10 minutes.

Title: Lasagna
Ingredients: Flour, butter, sugar, eggs, yeast
Description: Heat a pan over medium heat. Add 2 tablespoons of oil. Sauté 1 chopped onion until golden. Add 2 cloves of minced garlic and cook for 1 minute. Description: Heat a pan over medium heat. Add 2 tablespoons of oil. Sauté 1 chopped onion until golden. Add 2 cloves of minced garlic and cook for 1 minute. Stir in 1 teaspoon of salt, 1/2 teaspoon of pepper, and 1 teaspoon of paprika. Add 1 pound of chicken and cook until browned. Pour in 2 cups of broth and simmer for 20 minutes.

Title: Dal Tadka
Ingredients: Chicken, peanuts, chili peppers, soy sauce
Description: Boil 4 cups of water in a pot. Add 1 cup of rice and 1/2 teaspoon of salt. Cover and cook on low heat for 15 minutes. Fluff with a fork and serve.

Title: Shakshuka
Ingredients: Eggplant, zucchini, bell peppers, tomatoes, herbs
Description: Heat 3 tablespoons of oil in a pan. Add 1 sliced bell pepper and 1 diced tomato. Cook for 5 minutes. Add 1 cup of chopped chicken, 1 teaspoon of cumin, and 1/2 teaspoon of chili powder. Stir well and cook for another 10 minutes.

Title: Pelmeni
Ingredients: Flour, tomatoes, mozzarella, basil, olive oil
Description: Heat 3 tablespoons of oil in a pan. Add 1 sliced bell pepper and 1 diced tomato. Cook for 5 minutes. Add 1 cup of chopped chicken, 1 teaspoon of cumin, and 1/2 teaspoon of chili powder. Stir well and cook for another 10 minutes.

Title: Tempura
Ingredients: Chicken, bell peppers, pineapple, soy sauce
Description: Heat 3 tablespoons of oil in a pan. Add 1 sliced bell pepper and 1 diced tomato. Cook for 5 minutes. Add 1 cup of chopped chicken, 1 teaspoon of cumin, and 1/2 teaspoon of chili powder. Stir well and cook for another 10 minutes.

Title: Borscht
Ingredients: Eggplant, zucchini, bell peppers, tomatoes, herbs
Description: Boil 4 cups of water in a pot. Add 1 cup of rice and 1/2 teaspoon of salt. Cover and cook on low heat for 15 minutes. Fluff with a fork and serve.

Title: Kung Pao Chicken
Ingredients: Eggplant, zucchini, bell peppers, tomatoes, herbs
Description: Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C). Grease a baking dish with 1 tablespoon of butter. In a bowl, mix 2 cups of flour, 1 teaspoon of baking powder, and 1/2 teaspoon of salt. In another bowl, whisk 1 cup of milk, 1 egg, and 1/2 cup of sugar. Combine wet and dry ingredients, pour into the baking dish, and bake for 25 minutes.

Title: Egusi Soup

Description: Bring 6 cups of water to a boil. Add 2 cups of pasta and 1 teaspoon of salt. Cook for 10 minutes, then drain. In a saucepan, melt 2 tablespoons of butter, add 1/2 cup of cream, and 1/2 cup of grated cheese. Stir until smooth. Mix with the pasta and serve warm.

Title: Pounded Yam
Ingredients: Chicken, butter, cream, tomatoes, spices
Description: Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C). Grease a baking dish with 1 tablespoon of butter. In a bowl, mix 2 cups of flour, 1 teaspoon of baking powder, and 1/2 teaspoon of salt. In another bowl, whisk 1 cup of milk, 1 egg, and 1/2 cup of sugar. Combine wet and dry ingredients, pour into the baking dish, and bake for 25 minutes.

Title: Hummus
Ingredients: Shrimp, flour, eggs, tempura sauce
Description: Boil 4 cups of water in a pot. Add 1 cup of rice and 1/2 teaspoon of salt. Cover and cook on low heat for 15 minutes. Fluff with a fork and serve.

Title: Lasagna
Ingredients: Chicken, peanuts, chili peppers, soy sauce
Description: Marinate 1 pound of beef with 1 teaspoon of salt, 1/2 teaspoon of black pepper, and 1 tablespoon of soy sauce. Let it sit for 30 minutes. Heat a pan with 2 tablespoons of oil. Sear the beef for 5 minutes on each side. Reduce heat and cook for another 10 minutes, then serve.

Title: Tempura
Ingredients: Eggplant, zucchini, bell peppers, tomatoes, herbs
Description: Chop 2 potatoes, 1 carrot, and 1 onion. Heat 2 tablespoons of oil in a pot. Sauté the onion for 3 minutes. Add the potatoes and carrots, followed by 4 cups of vegetable broth. Season with 1 teaspoon of salt and 1/2 teaspoon of thyme. Simmer for 20 minutes until tender.

Title: Pelmeni
Ingredients: Egusi seeds, spinach, stockfish, palm oil
Description: Bring 6 cups of water to a boil. Add 2 cups of pasta and 1 teaspoon of salt. Cook for 10 minutes, then drain. In a saucepan, melt 2 tablespoons of butter, add 1/2 cup of cream, and 1/2 cup of grated cheese. Stir until smooth. Mix with the pasta and serve warm.

Title: Hummus
Ingredients: Yam flour, water

Description: Chop 2 potatoes, 1 carrot, and 1 onion. Heat 2 tablespoons of oil in a pot. Sauté the onion for 3 minutes. Add the potatoes and carrots, followed by 4 cups of vegetable broth. Season with 1 teaspoon of salt and 1/2 teaspoon of thyme. Simmer for 20 minutes until tender.

Title: Dal Tadka
Ingredients: Pasta, tomato sauce, cheese, ground beef, basil
Description: Heat a pan over medium heat. Add 2 tablespoons of oil. Sauté 1 chopped onion until golden. Add 2 cloves of minced garlic and cook for 1 minute. Title: Sweet and Sour Chicken
Ingredients: Flour, butter, sugar, eggs, yeast
Description: Heat 3 tablespoons of oil in a pan. Add 1 sliced bell pepper and 1 diced tomato. Cook for 5 minutes. Add 1 cup of chopped chicken, 1 teaspoon of cumin, and 1/2 teaspoon of chili powder. Stir well and cook for another 10 minutes.

Ingredients: Coconut milk, green curry paste, chicken, basil
Description: In a blender, combine 2 bananas, 1 cup of milk, 1/2 teaspoon of cinnamon, and 1 tablespoon of honey. Blend until smooth. Serve chilled.

Description: Boil 4 cups of water in a pot. Add 1 cup of rice and 1/2 teaspoon of salt. Cover and cook on low heat for 15 minutes. Fluff with a fork and serve.

Title: Croissant
Ingredients: Dough, ground meat, onions, salt, pepper
Description: Chop 2 potatoes, 1 carrot, and 1 onion. Heat 2 tablespoons of oil in a pot. Sauté the onion for 3 minutes. Add the potatoes and carrots, followed by 4 cups of vegetable broth. Season with 1 teaspoon of salt and 1/2 teaspoon of thyme. Simmer for 20 minutes until tender.

Title: Croissant
Ingredients: Tomatoes, eggs, onions, bell peppers, spices
Description: In a blender, combine 2 bananas, 1 cup of milk, 1/2 teaspoon of cinnamon, and 1 tablespoon of honey. Blend until smooth. Serve chilled.

Title: Pounded Yam
Ingredients: Beetroot, cabbage, potatoes, carrots, dill
Description: Heat 3 tablespoons of oil in a pan. Add 1 sliced bell pepper and 1 diced tomato. Cook for 5 minutes. Add 1 cup of chopped chicken, 1 teaspoon of cumin, and 1/2 teaspoon of chili powder. Stir well and cook for another 10 minutes.

Title: Pounded Yam
Ingredients: Flour, tomatoes, mozzarella, basil, olive oil
Description: Heat a pan over medium heat. Add 2 tablespoons of oil. Sauté 1 chopped onion until golden. Add 2 cloves of minced garlic and cook for 1 minute. Description: Chop 2 potatoes, 1 carrot, and 1 onion. Heat 2 tablespoons of oil in a pot. Sauté the onion for 3 minutes. Add the potatoes and carrots, followed by 4 cups of vegetable broth. Season with 1 teaspoon of salt and 1/2 teaspoon of thyme. Simmer for 20 minutes until tender.

Title: Tempura
Ingredients: Beetroot, cabbage, potatoes, carrots, dill
Description: Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C). Grease a baking dish with 1 tablespoon of butter. In a bowl, mix 2 cups of flour, 1 teaspoon of baking powder, and 1/2 teaspoon of salt. In another bowl, whisk 1 cup of milk, 1 egg, and 1/2 cup of sugar. Combine wet and dry ingredients, pour into the baking dish, and bake for 25 minutes.

Title: Pizza Margherita
Ingredients: Flour, tomatoes, mozzarella, basil, olive oil
Description: Bring 6 cups of water to a boil. Add 2 cups of pasta and 1 teaspoon of salt. Cook for 10 minutes, then drain. In a saucepan, melt 2 tablespoons of butter, add 1/2 cup of cream, and 1/2 cup of grated cheese. Stir until smooth. Mix with the pasta and serve warm.

Title: Croissant
Ingredients: Ground beef, lettuce, cheese, salsa, tortilla chips
Description: Heat a pan over medium heat. Add 2 tablespoons of oil. Sauté 1 chopped onion until golden. Add 2 cloves of minced garlic and cook for 1 minute. Stir in 1 teaspoon of salt, 1/2 teaspoon of pepper, and 1 teaspoon of paprika. Add 1 pound of chicken and cook until browned. Pour in 2 cups of broth and simmer for 20 minutes.

Title: Borscht
Ingredients: Tomatoes, eggs, onions, bell peppers, spices
Description: Boil 4 cups of water in a pot. Add 1 cup of rice and 1/2 teaspoon of salt. Cover and cook on low heat for 15 minutes. Fluff with a fork and serve.

Title: Egusi Soup
Ingredients: Pasta, tomato sauce, cheese, ground beef, basil
Description: Chop 2 potatoes, 1 carrot, and 1 onion. Heat 2 tablespoons of oil in a pot. Sauté the onion for 3 minutes. Add the potatoes and carrots, followed by 4 cups of vegetable broth. Season with 1 teaspoon of salt and 1/2 teaspoon of thyme. Simmer for 20 minutes until tender.

Title: Butter Chicken
Ingredients: Pasta, tomato sauce, cheese, ground beef, basil
Description: Heat 3 tablespoons of oil in a pan. Add 1 sliced bell pepper and 1 diced tomato. Cook for 5 minutes. Add 1 cup of chopped chicken, 1 teaspoon of cumin, and 1/2 teaspoon of chili powder. Stir well and cook for another 10 minutes.

Title: Pizza Margherita
Ingredients: Flour, tomatoes, mozzarella, basil, olive oil
Description: In a blender, combine 2 bananas, 1 cup of milk, 1/2 teaspoon of cinnamon, and 1 tablespoon of honey. Blend until smooth. Serve chilled.

Title: Taco Salad
Ingredients: Chicken, butter, cream, tomatoes, spices
Description: Marinate 1 pound of beef with 1 teaspoon of salt, 1/2 teaspoon of black pepper, and 1 tablespoon of soy sauce. Let it sit for 30 minutes. Heat a pan with 2 tablespoons of oil. Sear the beef for 5 minutes on each side. Reduce heat and cook for another 10 minutes, then serve.

Description: Marinate 1 pound of beef with 1 teaspoon of salt, 1/2 teaspoon of black pepper, and 1 tablespoon of soy sauce. Let it sit for 30 minutes. Heat a pan with 2 tablespoons of oil. Sear the beef for 5 minutes on each side. Reduce heat and cook for another 10 minutes, then serve.

Title: Egusi Soup
Ingredients: Flour, tomatoes, mozzarella, basil, olive oil
Description: Marinate 1 pound of beef with 1 teaspoon of salt, 1/2 teaspoon of black pepper, and 1 tablespoon of soy sauce. Let it sit for 30 minutes. Heat a pan with 2 tablespoons of oil. Sear the beef for 5 minutes on each side. Reduce heat and cook for another 10 minutes, then serve.

Title: Green Curry
Ingredients: Pasta, tomato sauce, cheese, ground beef, basil
Description: In a blender, combine 2 bananas, 1 cup of milk, 1/2 teaspoon of cinnamon, and 1 tablespoon of honey. Blend until smooth. Serve chilled.

Title: Burrito
Ingredients: Egusi seeds, spinach, stockfish, palm oil
Description: Bring 6 cups of water to a boil. Add 2 cups of pasta and 1 teaspoon of salt. Cook for 10 minutes, then drain. In a saucepan, melt 2 tablespoons of butter, add 1/2 cup of cream, and 1/2 cup of grated cheese. Stir until smooth. Mix with the pasta and serve warm.

Title: Pelmeni
Ingredients: Dough, ground meat, onions, salt, pepper
Description: Chop 2 potatoes, 1 carrot, and 1 onion. Heat 2 tablespoons of oil in a pot. Sauté the onion for 3 minutes. Add the potatoes and carrots, followed by 4 cups of vegetable broth. Season with 1 teaspoon of salt and 1/2 teaspoon of thyme. Simmer for 20 minutes until tender.

Title: Taco Salad
Ingredients: Ground beef, lettuce, cheese, salsa, tortilla chips

Title: Dal Tadka
Ingredients: Lentils, garlic, tomatoes, cumin, mustard seeds
Description: Heat a pan over medium heat. Add 2 tablespoons of oil. Sauté 1 chopped onion until golden. Add 2 cloves of minced garlic and cook for 1 minute. Description: Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C). Grease a baking dish with 1 tablespoon of butter. In a bowl, mix 2 cups of flour, 1 teaspoon of baking powder, and 1/2 teaspoon of salt. In another bowl, whisk 1 cup of milk, 1 egg, and 1/2 cup of sugar. Combine wet and dry ingredients, pour into the baking dish, and bake for 25 minutes.

Title: Pounded Yam
Ingredients: Pasta, tomato sauce, cheese, ground beef, basil
Description: Heat 3 tablespoons of oil in a pan. Add 1 sliced bell pepper and 1 diced tomato. Cook for 5 minutes. Add 1 cup of chopped chicken, 1 teaspoon of cumin, and 1/2 teaspoon of chili powder. Stir well and cook for another 10 minutes.

Title: Taco Salad
Ingredients: Pasta, tomato sauce, cheese, ground beef, basil
Description: Bring 6 cups of water to a boil. Add 2 cups of pasta and 1 teaspoon of salt. Cook for 10 minutes, then drain. In a saucepan, melt 2 tablespoons of butter, add 1/2 cup of cream, and 1/2 cup of grated cheese. Stir until smooth. Mix with the pasta and serve warm.

Title: Borscht
Ingredients: Shrimp, lemongrass, lime leaves, chili, broth
Description: Heat a pan over medium heat. Add 2 tablespoons of oil. Sauté 1 chopped onion until golden. Add 2 cloves of minced garlic and cook for 1 minute. Stir in 1 teaspoon of salt, 1/2 teaspoon of pepper, and 1 teaspoon of paprika. Add 1 pound of chicken and cook until browned. Pour in 2 cups of broth and simmer for 20 minutes.

Title: Tempura
Ingredients: Coconut milk, green curry paste, chicken, basil
Description: Chop 2 potatoes, 1 carrot, and 1 onion. Heat 2 tablespoons of oil in a pot. Sauté the onion for 3 minutes. Add the potatoes and carrots, followed by 4 cups of vegetable broth. Season with 1 teaspoon of salt and 1/2 teaspoon of thyme. Simmer for 20 minutes until tender.

Title: Tom Yum Soup
Ingredients: Noodles, broth, pork, egg, green onions
Description: Heat 3 tablespoons of oil in a pan. Add 1 sliced bell pepper and 1 diced tomato. Cook for 5 minutes. Add 1 cup of chopped chicken, 1 teaspoon of cumin, and 1/2 teaspoon of chili powder. Stir well and cook for another 10 minutes.

Description: Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C). Grease a baking dish with 1 tablespoon of butter. In a bowl, mix 2 cups of flour, 1 teaspoon of baking powder, and 1/2 teaspoon of salt. In another bowl, whisk 1 cup of milk, 1 egg, and 1/2 cup of sugar. Combine wet and dry ingredients, pour into the baking dish, and bake for 25 minutes.

Title: Lasagna
Ingredients: Yam flour, water
Description: Heat 3 tablespoons of oil in a pan. Add 1 sliced bell pepper and 1 diced tomato. Cook for 5 minutes. Add 1 cup of chopped chicken, 1 teaspoon of cumin, and 1/2 teaspoon of chili powder. Stir well and cook for another 10 minutes.

Title: Pounded Yam
Ingredients: Flour, butter, sugar, eggs, yeast
Description: In a blender, combine 2 bananas, 1 cup of milk, 1/2 teaspoon of cinnamon, and 1 tablespoon of honey. Blend until smooth. Serve chilled.

Title: Taco Salad
Ingredients: Noodles, broth, pork, egg, green onions
Description: Marinate 1 pound of beef with 1 teaspoon of salt, 1/2 teaspoon of black pepper, and 1 tablespoon of soy sauce. Let it sit for 30 minutes. Heat a pan with 2 tablespoons of oil. Sear the beef for 5 minutes on each side. Reduce heat and cook for another 10 minutes, then serve.

Title: Ratatouille
Ingredients: Chicken, butter, cream, tomatoes, spices
Description: Bring 6 cups of water to a boil. Add 2 cups of pasta and 1 teaspoon of salt. Cook for 10 minutes, then drain. In a saucepan, melt 2 tablespoons of butter, add 1/2 cup of cream, and 1/2 cup of grated cheese. Stir until smooth. Mix with the pasta and serve warm.

Title: Green Curry
Ingredients: Ground beef, lettuce, cheese, salsa, tortilla chips
Description: Marinate 1 pound of beef with 1 teaspoon of salt, 1/2 teaspoon of black pepper, and 1 tablespoon of soy sauce. Let it sit for 30 minutes. Heat a pan with 2 tablespoons of oil. Sear the beef for 5 minutes on each side. Reduce heat and cook for another 10 minutes, then serve.

Title: Tempura
Ingredients: Chicken, butter, cream, tomatoes, spices
Description: Chop 2 potatoes, 1 carrot, and 1 onion. Heat 2 tablespoons of oil in a pot. Sauté the onion for 3 minutes. Add the potatoes and carrots, followed by 4 cups of vegetable broth. Season with 1 teaspoon of salt and 1/2 teaspoon of thyme. Simmer for 20 minutes until tender.

Description: In a blender, combine 2 bananas, 1 cup of milk, 1/2 teaspoon of cinnamon, and 1 tablespoon of honey. Blend until smooth. Serve chilled.

Title: Ramen
Ingredients: Egusi seeds, spinach, stockfish, palm oil
Description: Heat 3 tablespoons of oil in a pan. Add 1 sliced bell pepper and 1 diced tomato. Cook for 5 minutes. Add 1 cup of chopped chicken, 1 teaspoon of cumin, and 1/2 teaspoon of chili powder. Stir well and cook for another 10 minutes.

Title: Ratatouille
Ingredients: Shrimp, lemongrass, lime leaves, chili, broth
Description: Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C). Grease a baking dish with 1 tablespoon of butter. In a bowl, mix 2 cups of flour, 1 teaspoon of baking powder, and 1/2 teaspoon of salt. Description: Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C). Grease a baking dish with 1 tablespoon of butter. In a bowl, mix 2 cups of flour, 1 teaspoon of baking powder, and 1/2 teaspoon of salt. In another bowl, whisk 1 cup of milk, 1 egg, and 1/2 cup of sugar. Combine wet and dry ingredients, pour into the baking dish, and bake for 25 minutes.

Title: Tempura
Ingredients: Lentils, garlic, tomatoes, cumin, mustard seeds
Description: In a blender, combine 2 bananas, 1 cup of milk, 1/2 teaspoon of cinnamon, and 1 tablespoon of honey. Blend until smooth. Serve chilled.

Title: Pounded Yam
Ingredients: Chicken, peanuts, chili peppers, soy sauce
Description: Bring 6 cups of water to a boil. Add 2 cups of pasta and 1 teaspoon of salt. Cook for 10 minutes, then drain. In a saucepan, melt 2 tablespoons of butter, add 1/2 cup of cream, and 1/2 cup of grated cheese. Stir until smooth. Mix with the pasta and serve warm.

Title: Borscht
Ingredients: Tortilla, beans, rice, cheese, chicken
Description: Chop 2 potatoes, 1 carrot, and 1 onion. Heat 2 tablespoons of oil in a pot. Sauté the onion for 3 minutes. Add the potatoes and carrots, followed by 4 cups of vegetable broth. Season with 1 teaspoon of salt and 1/2 teaspoon of thyme. Simmer for 20 minutes until tender.

Title: Egusi Soup
Ingredients: Pasta, tomato sauce, cheese, ground beef, basil
Description: Heat a pan over medium heat. Add 2 tablespoons of oil. Sauté 1 chopped onion until golden. Add 2 cloves of minced garlic and cook for 1 minute. Description: Bring 6 cups of water to a boil. Add 2 cups of pasta and 1 teaspoon of salt. Cook for 10 minutes, then drain. In a saucepan, melt 2 tablespoons of butter, add 1/2 cup of cream, and 1/2 cup of grated cheese. Stir until smooth. Mix with the pasta and serve warm.

Title: Hummus
Ingredients: Dough, ground meat, onions, salt, pepper
Description: In a blender, combine 2 bananas, 1 cup of milk, 1/2 teaspoon of cinnamon, and 1 tablespoon of honey. Blend until smooth. Serve chilled.

Title: Burrito
Ingredients: Ground beef, lettuce, cheese, salsa, tortilla chips
Description: Chop 2 potatoes, 1 carrot, and 1 onion. Heat 2 tablespoons of oil in a pot. Sauté the onion for 3 minutes. Add the potatoes and carrots, followed by 4 cups of vegetable broth. Season with 1 teaspoon of salt and 1/2 teaspoon of thyme. Simmer for 20 minutes until tender.

Title: Pizza Margherita
Ingredients: Shrimp, lemongrass, lime leaves, chili, broth
Description: Marinate 1 pound of beef with 1 teaspoon of salt, 1/2 teaspoon of black pepper, and 1 tablespoon of soy sauce. Let it sit for 30 minutes. Heat a pan with 2 tablespoons of oil. Sear the beef for 5 minutes on each side. Reduce heat and cook for another 10 minutes, then serve.

Title: Lasagna
Ingredients: Chicken, peanuts, chili peppers, soy sauce
Description: Boil 4 cups of water in a pot. Add 1 cup of rice and 1/2 teaspoon of salt. Cover and cook on low heat for 15 minutes. Fluff with a fork and serve.

Title: Croissant
Ingredients: Yam flour, water
Description: Chop 2 potatoes, 1 carrot, and 1 onion. Heat 2 tablespoons of oil in a pot. Sauté the onion for 3 minutes. Add the potatoes and carrots, followed by 4 cups of vegetable broth. Season with 1 teaspoon of salt and 1/2 teaspoon of thyme. Simmer for 20 minutes until tender.

Title: Pelmeni
Ingredients: Chicken, bell peppers, pineapple, soy sauce
Description: Boil 4 cups of water in a pot. Add 1 cup of rice and 1/2 teaspoon of salt. Cover and cook on low heat for 15 minutes. Fluff with a fork and serve.

Title: Green Curry
Ingredients: Shrimp, lemongrass, lime leaves, chili, broth
Description: Bring 6 cups of water to a boil. Add 2 cups of pasta and 1 teaspoon of salt. Cook for 10 minutes, then drain. In a saucepan, melt 2 tablespoons of butter, add 1/2 cup of cream, and 1/2 cup of grated cheese. Stir until smooth. Mix with the pasta and serve warm.

Title: Ramen
Ingredients: Chickpeas, tahini, lemon, garlic, olive oil
Description: Heat 3 tablespoons of oil in a pan. Add 1 sliced bell pepper and 1 diced tomato. Cook for 5 minutes. Add 1 cup of chopped chicken, 1 teaspoon of cumin, and 1/2 teaspoon of chili powder. Stir well and cook for another 10 minutes.

Title: Dal Tadka
Ingredients: Egusi seeds, spinach, stockfish, palm oil
Description: Heat a pan over medium heat. Add 2 tablespoons of oil. Sauté 1 chopped onion until golden. Add 2 cloves of minced garlic and cook for 1 minute. Stir in 1 teaspoon of salt, 1/2 teaspoon of pepper, and 1 teaspoon of paprika. Add 1 pound of chicken and cook until browned. Pour in 2 cups of broth and simmer for 20 minutes.

Description: Chop 2 potatoes, 1 carrot, and 1 onion. Heat 2 tablespoons of oil in a pot. Sauté the onion for 3 minutes. Add the potatoes and carrots, followed by 4 cups of vegetable broth. Season with 1 teaspoon of salt and 1/2 teaspoon of thyme. Simmer for 20 minutes until tender.

Title: Burrito
Ingredients: Tomatoes, eggs, onions, bell peppers, spices
Description: Heat 3 tablespoons of oil in a pan. Add 1 sliced bell pepper and 1 diced tomato. Cook for 5 minutes. Add 1 cup of chopped chicken, 1 teaspoon of cumin, and 1/2 teaspoon of chili powder. Stir well and cook for another 10 minutes.

Title: Burrito
Ingredients: Flour, tomatoes, mozzarella, basil, olive oil
Description: Heat a pan over medium heat. Add 2 tablespoons of oil. Sauté 1 chopped onion until golden. Add 2 cloves of minced garlic and cook for 1 minute. Stir in 1 teaspoon of salt, 1/2 teaspoon of pepper, and 1 teaspoon of paprika. Add 1 pound of chicken and cook until browned. Pour in 2 cups of broth and simmer for 20 minutes.

Title: Pounded Yam
Ingredients: Pasta, tomato sauce, cheese, ground beef, basil
Description: Boil 4 cups of water in a pot. Add 1 cup of rice and 1/2 teaspoon of salt. Cover and cook on low heat for 15 minutes. Fluff with a fork and serve.

Title: Croissant
Ingredients: Shrimp, flour, eggs, tempura sauce
Description: Heat a pan over medium heat. Add 2 tablespoons of oil. Sauté 1 chopped onion until golden. Add 2 cloves of minced garlic and cook for 1 minute. Stir in 1 teaspoon of salt, 1/2 teaspoon of pepper, and 1 teaspoon of paprika. Add 1 pound of chicken and cook until browned. Pour in 2 cups of broth and simmer for 20 minutes.

Title: Pelmeni
Ingredients: Pasta, tomato sauce, cheese, ground beef, basil
Description: Marinate 1 pound of beef with 1 teaspoon of salt, 1/2 teaspoon of black pepper, and 1 tablespoon of soy sauce. Let it sit for 30 minutes. Heat a pan with 2 tablespoons of oil. Sear the beef for 5 minutes on each side. Reduce heat and cook for another 10 minutes, then serve.

Title: Egusi Soup
Ingredients: Shrimp, flour, eggs, tempura sauce
Description: In a blender, combine 2 bananas, 1 cup of milk, 1/2 teaspoon of cinnamon, and 1 tablespoon of honey. Blend until smooth. Serve chilled.

Title: Pizza Margherita

Description: Heat 3 tablespoons of oil in a pan. Add 1 sliced bell pepper and 1 diced tomato. Cook for 5 minutes. Add 1 cup of chopped chicken, 1 teaspoon of cumin, and 1/2 teaspoon of chili powder. Stir well and cook for another 10 minutes.

Title: Sweet and Sour Chicken
Ingredients: Pasta, tomato sauce, cheese, ground beef, basil
Description: Heat 3 tablespoons of oil in a pan. Add 1 sliced bell pepper and 1 diced tomato. Cook for 5 minutes. Add 1 cup of chopped chicken, 1 teaspoon of cumin, and 1/2 teaspoon of chili powder. Stir well and cook for another 10 minutes.

Title: Pizza Margherita
Ingredients: Lentils, garlic, tomatoes, cumin, mustard seeds
Description: Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C). Grease a baking dish with 1 tablespoon of butter. In a bowl, mix 2 cups of flour, 1 teaspoon of baking powder, and 1/2 teaspoon of salt. In another bowl, whisk 1 cup of milk, 1 egg, and 1/2 cup of sugar. Combine wet and dry ingredients, pour into the baking dish, and bake for 25 minutes.

Title: Tempura
Ingredients: Coconut milk, green curry paste, chicken, basil
Description: Heat 3 tablespoons of oil in a pan. Add 1 sliced bell pepper and 1 diced tomato. Cook for 5 minutes. Add 1 cup of chopped chicken, 1 teaspoon of cumin, and 1/2 teaspoon of chili powder. Stir well and cook for another 10 minutes.

Title: Pelmeni
Ingredients: Ground beef, lettuce, cheese, salsa, tortilla chips
Description: Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C). Grease a baking dish with 1 tablespoon of butter. In a bowl, mix 2 cups of flour, 1 teaspoon of baking powder, and 1/2 teaspoon of salt. In another bowl, whisk 1 cup of milk, 1 egg, and 1/2 cup of sugar. Combine wet and dry ingredients, pour into the baking dish, and bake for 25 minutes.

Title: Dal Tadka
Ingredients: Dough, ground meat, onions, salt, pepper
Description: Heat a pan over medium heat. Add 2 tablespoons of oil. Sauté 1 chopped onion until golden. Add 2 cloves of minced garlic and cook for 1 minute. Stir in 1 teaspoon of salt, 1/2 teaspoon of pepper, and 1 teaspoon of paprika. Add 1 pound of chicken and cook until browned. Pour in 2 cups of broth and simmer for 20 minutes.

Title: Shakshuka
Ingredients: Flour, tomatoes, mozzarella, basil, olive oil
Description: Boil 4 cups of water in a pot. Add 1 cup of rice and 1/2 teaspoon of salt. Cover and cook on low heat for 15 minutes. Fluff with a fork and serve.

Title: Pounded Yam
Ingredients: Flour, butter, sugar, eggs, yeast
Description: In a blender, combine 2 bananas, 1 cup of milk, 1/2 teaspoon of cinnamon, and 1 tablespoon of honey. Blend until smooth. Serve chilled.

Title: Ratatouille
Ingredients: Flour, butter, sugar, eggs, yeast
Description: Chop 2 potatoes, 1 carrot, and 1 onion. Heat 2 tablespoons of oil in a pot. Sauté the onion for 3 minutes. Add the potatoes and carrots, followed by 4 cups of vegetable broth. Season with 1 teaspoon of salt and 1/2 teaspoon of thyme. Simmer for 20 minutes until tender.

Title: Ramen
Ingredients: Chicken, peanuts, chili peppers, soy sauce
Description: Bring 6 cups of water to a boil. Add 2 cups of pasta and 1 teaspoon of salt. Cook for 10 minutes, then drain. In a saucepan, melt 2 tablespoons of butter, add 1/2 cup of cream, and 1/2 cup of grated cheese. Stir until smooth. Mix with the pasta and serve warm.

Title: Borscht
Ingredients: Noodles, broth, pork, egg, green onions
Description: Heat 3 tablespoons of oil in a pan. Add 1 sliced bell pepper and 1 diced tomato. Cook for 5 minutes. Add 1 cup of chopped chicken, 1 teaspoon of cumin, and 1/2 teaspoon of chili powder. Stir well and cook for another 10 minutes.

Description: Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C). Grease a baking dish with 1 tablespoon of butter. In a bowl, mix 2 cups of flour, 1 teaspoon of baking powder, and 1/2 teaspoon of salt. In another bowl, whisk 1 cup of milk, 1 egg, and 1/2 cup of sugar. Combine wet and dry ingredients, pour into the baking dish, and bake for 25 minutes.

Title: Lasagna
Ingredients: Ground beef, lettuce, cheese, salsa, tortilla chips
Description: Heat a pan over medium heat. Add 2 tablespoons of oil. Sauté 1 chopped onion until golden. Add 2 cloves of minced garlic and cook for 1 minute. Stir in 1 teaspoon of salt, 1/2 teaspoon of pepper, and 1 teaspoon of paprika. Add 1 pound of chicken and cook until browned. Pour in 2 cups of broth and simmer for 20 minutes.

Title: Green Curry
Ingredients: Chicken, peanuts, chili peppers, soy sauce
Description: Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C). Grease a baking dish with 1 tablespoon of butter. In a bowl, mix 2 cups of flour, 1 teaspoon of baking powder, and 1/2 teaspoon of salt. In another bowl, whisk 1 cup of milk, 1 egg, and 1/2 cup of sugar. Combine wet and dry ingredients, pour into the baking dish, and bake for 25 minutes.

Title: Borscht
Ingredients: Beetroot, cabbage, potatoes, carrots, dill
Description: Chop 2 potatoes, 1 carrot, and 1 onion. Heat 2 tablespoons of oil in a pot. Sauté the onion for 3 minutes. Add the potatoes and carrots, followed by 4 cups of vegetable broth. Season with 1 teaspoon of salt and 1/2 teaspoon of thyme. Simmer for 20 minutes until tender.

Title: Burrito
Ingredients: Shrimp, lemongrass, lime leaves, chili, broth
Description: Bring 6 cups of water to a boil. Add 2 cups of pasta and 1 teaspoon of salt. Cook for 10 minutes, then drain. In a saucepan, melt 2 tablespoons of butter, add 1/2 cup of cream, and 1/2 cup of grated cheese. Stir until smooth. Mix with the pasta and serve warm.

Title: Shakshuka
Ingredients: Chicken, bell peppers, pineapple, soy sauce
Description: Bring 6 cups of water to a boil. Add 2 cups of pasta and 1 teaspoon of salt. Cook for 10 minutes, then drain. In a saucepan, melt 2 tablespoons of butter, add 1/2 cup of cream, and 1/2 cup of grated cheese. Stir until smooth. Mix with the pasta and serve warm.

Title: Pizza Margherita
Ingredients: Chicken, bell peppers, pineapple, soy sauce
Description: In a blender, combine 2 bananas, 1 cup of milk, 1/2 teaspoon of cinnamon, and 1 tablespoon of honey. Blend until smooth. Serve chilled.

Title: Egusi Soup
Ingredients: Tomatoes, eggs, onions, bell peppers, spices
Description: Boil 4 cups of water in a pot. Add 1 cup of rice and 1/2 teaspoon of salt. Cover and cook on low heat for 15 minutes. Fluff with a fork and serve.

Title: Taco Salad
Ingredients: Shrimp, lemongrass, lime leaves, chili, broth
Description: Heat 3 tablespoons of oil in a pan. Add 1 sliced bell pepper and 1 diced tomato. Cook for 5 minutes. Add 1 cup of chopped chicken, 1 teaspoon of cumin, and 1/2 teaspoon of chili powder. Stir well and cook for another 10 minutes.

Title: Kung Pao Chicken
Ingredients: Chickpeas, tahini, lemon, garlic, olive oil
Description: Boil 4 cups of water in a pot. Add 1 cup of rice and 1/2 teaspoon of salt. Cover and cook on low heat for 15 minutes. Fluff with a fork and serve.

Title: Ratatouille
Ingredients: Shrimp, lemongrass, lime leaves, chili, broth
Description: In a blender, combine 2 bananas, 1 cup of milk, 1/2 teaspoon of cinnamon, and 1 tablespoon of honey. Blend until smooth. Serve chilled.

Ingredients: Chicken, bell peppers, pineapple, soy sauce
Description: Chop 2 potatoes, 1 carrot, and 1 onion. Heat 2 tablespoons of oil in a pot. Sauté the onion for 3 minutes. Add the potatoes and carrots, followed by 4 cups of vegetable broth. Season with 1 teaspoon of salt and 1/2 teaspoon of thyme. Simmer for 20 minutes until tender.

Description: In a blender, combine 2 bananas, 1 cup of milk, 1/2 teaspoon of cinnamon, and 1 tablespoon of honey. Blend until smooth. Serve chilled.

Title: Tom Yum Soup
Ingredients: Chicken, peanuts, chili peppers, soy sauce
Description: Marinate 1 pound of beef with 1 teaspoon of salt, 1/2 teaspoon of black pepper, and 1 tablespoon of soy sauce. Let it sit for 30 minutes. Heat a pan with 2 tablespoons of oil. Sear the beef for 5 minutes on each side. Reduce heat and cook for another 10 minutes, then serve.

Title: Ratatouille
Ingredients: Beetroot, cabbage, potatoes, carrots, dill
Description: Boil 4 cups of water in a pot. Add 1 cup of rice and 1/2 teaspoon of salt. Cover and cook on low heat for 15 minutes. Fluff with a fork and serve.

Title: Tempura
Ingredients: Eggplant, zucchini, bell peppers, tomatoes, herbs

Description: Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C). Grease a baking dish with 1 tablespoon of butter. In a bowl, mix 2 cups of flour, 1 teaspoon of baking powder, and 1/2 teaspoon of salt. In another bowl, whisk 1 cup of milk, 1 egg, and 1/2 cup of sugar. Combine wet and dry ingredients, pour into the baking dish, and bake for 25 minutes.

Title: Butter Chicken
Ingredients: Chicken, bell peppers, pineapple, soy sauce
Description: Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C). Grease a baking dish with 1 tablespoon of butter. In a bowl, mix 2 cups of flour, 1 teaspoon of baking powder, and 1/2 teaspoon of salt. In another bowl, whisk 1 cup of milk, 1 egg, and 1/2 cup of sugar. Combine wet and dry ingredients, pour into the baking dish, and bake for 25 minutes.

Title: Kung Pao Chicken
Ingredients: Chicken, bell peppers, pineapple, soy sauce
Description: In a blender, combine 2 bananas, 1 cup of milk, 1/2 teaspoon of cinnamon, and 1 tablespoon of honey. Blend until smooth. Serve chilled.

Title: Taco Salad
Ingredients: Shrimp, flour, eggs, tempura sauce
Description: Heat a pan over medium heat. Add 2 tablespoons of oil. Sauté 1 chopped onion until golden. Add 2 cloves of minced garlic and cook for 1 minute. Stir in 1 teaspoon of salt, 1/2 teaspoon of pepper, and 1 teaspoon of paprika. Add 1 pound of chicken and cook until browned. Pour in 2 cups of broth and simmer for 20 minutes.

Title: Lasagna
Ingredients: Flour, tomatoes, mozzarella, basil, olive oil
Description: Marinate 1 pound of beef with 1 teaspoon of salt, 1/2 teaspoon of black pepper, and 1 tablespoon of soy sauce. Let it sit for 30 minutes. Heat a pan with 2 tablespoons of oil. Sear the beef for 5 minutes on each side. Reduce heat and cook for another 10 minutes, then serve.

Title: Pounded Yam
Ingredients: Flour, tomatoes, mozzarella, basil, olive oil
Description: Bring 6 cups of water to a boil. Add 2 cups of pasta and 1 teaspoon of salt. Cook for 10 minutes, then drain. In a saucepan, melt 2 tablespoons of butter, add 1/2 cup of cream, and 1/2 cup of grated cheese. Stir until smooth. Mix with the pasta and serve warm.

Description: Heat 3 tablespoons of oil in a pan. Add 1 sliced bell pepper and 1 diced tomato. Cook for 5 minutes. Add 1 cup of chopped chicken, 1 teaspoon of cumin, and 1/2 teaspoon of chili powder. Stir well and cook for another 10 minutes.

Title: Burrito
Ingredients: Flour, tomatoes, mozzarella, basil, olive oil
Description: Heat a pan over medium heat. Add 2 tablespoons of oil. Sauté 1 chopped onion until golden. Add 2 cloves of minced garlic and cook for 1 minute. Stir in 1 teaspoon of salt, 1/2 teaspoon of pepper, and 1 teaspoon of paprika. Add 1 pound of chicken and cook until browned. Pour in 2 cups of broth and simmer for 20 minutes.

Title: Pounded Yam
Ingredients: Tomatoes, eggs, onions, bell peppers, spices
Description: Heat 3 tablespoons of oil in a pan. Add 1 sliced bell pepper and 1 diced tomato. Cook for 5 minutes. Add 1 cup of chopped chicken, 1 teaspoon of cumin, and 1/2 teaspoon of chili powder. Stir well and cook for another 10 minutes.

Title: Ratatouille
Ingredients: Tortilla, beans, rice, cheese, chicken
Description: Chop 2 potatoes, 1 carrot, and 1 onion. Heat 2 tablespoons of oil in a pot. Sauté the onion for 3 minutes. Add the potatoes and carrots, followed by 4 cups of vegetable broth. Season with 1 teaspoon of salt and 1/2 teaspoon of thyme. Simmer for 20 minutes until tender.

Title: Tempura
Ingredients: Flour, butter, sugar, eggs, yeast
Description: Chop 2 potatoes, 1 carrot, and 1 onion. Heat 2 tablespoons of oil in a pot. Sauté the onion for 3 minutes. Add the potatoes and carrots, followed by 4 cups of vegetable broth. Season with 1 teaspoon of salt and 1/2 teaspoon of thyme. Simmer for 20 minutes until tender.

Description: Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C). Grease a baking dish with 1 tablespoon of butter. In a bowl, mix 2 cups of flour, 1 teaspoon of baking powder, and 1/2 teaspoon of salt. In another bowl, whisk 1 cup of milk, 1 egg, and 1/2 cup of sugar. Combine wet and dry ingredients, pour into the baking dish, and bake for 25 minutes.

Title: Croissant
Ingredients: Ground beef, lettuce, cheese, salsa, tortilla chips
Description: Bring 6 cups of water to a boil. Add 2 cups of pasta and 1 teaspoon of salt. Cook for 10 minutes, then drain. In a saucepan, melt 2 tablespoons of butter, add 1/2 cup of cream, and 1/2 cup of grated cheese. Stir until smooth. Mix with the pasta and serve warm.

Title: Hummus
Ingredients: Tortilla, beans, rice, cheese, chicken
Description: In a blender, combine 2 bananas, 1 cup of milk, 1/2 teaspoon of cinnamon, and 1 tablespoon of honey. Blend until smooth. Serve chilled.

Title: Egusi Soup
Ingredients: Coconut milk, green curry paste, chicken, basil
Description: Boil 4 cups of water in a pot. Add 1 cup of rice and 1/2 teaspoon of salt. Cover and cook on low heat for 15 minutes. Fluff with a fork and serve.

Title: Hummus
Ingredients: Chicken, bell peppers, pineapple, soy sauce
Description: Heat 3 tablespoons of oil in a pan. Add 1 sliced bell pepper and 1 diced tomato. Cook for 5 minutes. Add 1 cup of chopped chicken, 1 teaspoon of cumin, and 1/2 teaspoon of chili powder. Stir well and cook for another 10 minutes.

Title: Sweet and Sour Chicken
Ingredients: Tomatoes, eggs, onions, bell peppers, spices
Description: Heat a pan over medium heat. Add 2 tablespoons of oil. Sauté 1 chopped onion until golden. Add 2 cloves of minced garlic and cook for 1 minute. Stir in 1 teaspoon of salt, 1/2 teaspoon of pepper, and 1 teaspoon of paprika. Add 1 pound of chicken and cook until browned. Pour in 2 cups of broth and simmer for 20 minutes.

Title: Ratatouille
Ingredients: Tomatoes, eggs, onions, bell peppers, spices
Description: Heat 3 tablespoons of oil in a pan. Add 1 sliced bell pepper and 1 diced tomato. Cook for 5 minutes. Add 1 cup of chopped chicken, 1 teaspoon of cumin, and 1/2 teaspoon of chili powder. Stir well and cook for another 10 minutes.

Title: Egusi Soup
Ingredients: Noodles, broth, pork, egg, green onions
Description: Marinate 1 pound of beef with 1 teaspoon of salt, 1/2 teaspoon of black pepper, and 1 tablespoon of soy sauce. Let it sit for 30 minutes. Heat a pan with 2 tablespoons of oil. Sear the beef for 5 minutes on each side. Reduce heat and cook for another 10 minutes, then serve.

Title: Borscht
Ingredients: Chickpeas, tahini, lemon, garlic, olive oil
Description: Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C). Grease a baking dish with 1 tablespoon of butter. In a bowl, mix 2 cups of flour, 1 teaspoon of baking powder, and 1/2 teaspoon of salt. In another bowl, whisk 1 cup of milk, 1 egg, and 1/2 cup of sugar. Combine wet and dry ingredients, pour into the baking dish, and bake for 25 minutes.

Title: Dal Tadka
Ingredients: Shrimp, flour, eggs, tempura sauce
Description: Chop 2 potatoes, 1 carrot, and 1 onion. Heat 2 tablespoons of oil in a pot. Sauté the onion for 3 minutes. Add the potatoes and carrots, followed by 4 cups of vegetable broth. Season with 1 teaspoon of salt and 1/2 teaspoon of thyme. Simmer for 20 minutes until tender.

Description: In a blender, combine 2 bananas, 1 cup of milk, 1/2 teaspoon of cinnamon, and 1 tablespoon of honey. Blend until smooth. Serve chilled.

Title: Lasagna
Ingredients: Flour, butter, sugar, eggs, yeast
Description: Marinate 1 pound of beef with 1 teaspoon of salt, 1/2 teaspoon of black pepper, and 1 tablespoon of soy sauce. Let it sit for 30 minutes. Heat a pan with 2 tablespoons of oil. Sear the beef for 5 minutes on each side. Reduce heat and cook for another 10 minutes, then serve.

Title: Kung Pao Chicken
Ingredients: Flour, butter, sugar, eggs, yeast
Description: Heat 3 tablespoons of oil in a pan. Add 1 sliced bell pepper and 1 diced tomato. Cook for 5 minutes. Add 1 cup of chopped chicken, 1 teaspoon of cumin, and 1/2 teaspoon of chili powder. Stir well and cook for another 10 minutes.

Title: Pounded Yam

Description: Heat 3 tablespoons of oil in a pan. Add 1 sliced bell pepper and 1 diced tomato. Cook for 5 minutes. Add 1 cup of chopped chicken, 1 teaspoon of cumin, and 1/2 teaspoon of chili powder. Stir well and cook for another 10 minutes.

Title: Hummus
Ingredients: Egusi seeds, spinach, stockfish, palm oil
Description: Heat a pan over medium heat. Add 2 tablespoons of oil. Sauté 1 chopped onion until golden. Add 2 cloves of minced garlic and cook for 1 minute. Stir in 1 teaspoon of salt, 1/2 teaspoon of pepper, and 1 teaspoon of paprika. Add 1 pound of chicken and cook until browned. Pour in 2 cups of broth and simmer for 20 minutes.

Title: Butter Chicken
Ingredients: Noodles, broth, pork, egg, green onions
Description: Boil 4 cups of water in a pot. Add 1 cup of rice and 1/2 teaspoon of salt. Cover and cook on low heat for 15 minutes. Fluff with a fork and serve.

Description: Boil 4 cups of water in a pot. Add 1 cup of rice and 1/2 teaspoon of salt. Cover and cook on low heat for 15 minutes. Fluff with a fork and serve.

Title: Lasagna
Ingredients: Pasta, tomato sauce, cheese, ground beef, basil
Description: Bring 6 cups of water to a boil. Add 2 cups of pasta and 1 teaspoon of salt. Cook for 10 minutes, then drain. In a saucepan, melt 2 tablespoons of butter, add 1/2 cup of cream, and 1/2 cup of grated cheese. Stir until smooth. Mix with the pasta and serve warm.

Title: Pizza Margherita
Ingredients: Chicken, peanuts, chili peppers, soy sauce
Description: Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C). Grease a baking dish with 1 tablespoon of butter. In a bowl, mix 2 cups of flour, 1 teaspoon of baking powder, and 1/2 teaspoon of salt. In another bowl, whisk 1 cup of milk, 1 egg, and 1/2 cup of sugar. Combine wet and dry ingredients, pour into the baking dish, and bake for 25 minutes.

Title: Lasagna
Ingredients: Eggplant, zucchini, bell peppers, tomatoes, herbs
Description: Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C). Grease a baking dish with 1 tablespoon of butter. In a bowl, mix 2 cups of flour, 1 teaspoon of baking powder, and 1/2 teaspoon of salt. Title: Burrito

Title: Pounded Yam
Ingredients: Chicken, peanuts, chili peppers, soy sauce
Description: Chop 2 potatoes, 1 carrot, and 1 onion. Heat 2 tablespoons of oil in a pot. Sauté the onion for 3 minutes. Add the potatoes and carrots, followed by 4 cups of vegetable broth. Season with 1 teaspoon of salt and 1/2 teaspoon of thyme. Simmer for 20 minutes until tender.

Description: Marinate 1 pound of beef with 1 teaspoon of salt, 1/2 teaspoon of black pepper, and 1 tablespoon of soy sauce. Let it sit for 30 minutes. Heat a pan with 2 tablespoons of oil. Sear the beef for 5 minutes on each side. Reduce heat and cook for another 10 minutes, then serve.

Title: Lasagna
Ingredients: Shrimp, flour, eggs, tempura sauce
Description: Marinate 1 pound of beef with 1 teaspoon of salt, 1/2 teaspoon of black pepper, and 1 tablespoon of soy sauce. Let it sit for 30 minutes. Heat a pan with 2 tablespoons of oil. Sear the beef for 5 minutes on each side. Reduce heat and cook for another 10 minutes, then serve.

Title: Kung Pao Chicken
Ingredients: Coconut milk, green curry paste, chicken, basil
Description: Heat a pan over medium heat. Add 2 tablespoons of oil. Sauté 1 chopped onion until golden. Add 2 cloves of minced garlic and cook for 1 minute. Stir in 1 teaspoon of salt, 1/2 teaspoon of pepper, and 1 teaspoon of paprika. Add 1 pound of chicken and cook until browned. Pour in 2 cups of broth and simmer for 20 minutes.

Title: Dal Tadka
Ingredients: Beetroot, cabbage, potatoes, carrots, dill
Description: Chop 2 potatoes, 1 carrot, and 1 onion. Heat 2 tablespoons of oil in a pot. Sauté the onion for 3 minutes. Add the potatoes and carrots, followed by 4 cups of vegetable broth. Season with 1 teaspoon of salt and 1/2 teaspoon of thyme. Simmer for 20 minutes until tender.

Title: Taco Salad
Ingredients: Yam flour, water
Description: Heat a pan over medium heat. Add 2 tablespoons of oil. Sauté 1 chopped onion until golden. Add 2 cloves of minced garlic and cook for 1 minute. Stir in 1 teaspoon of salt, 1/2 teaspoon of pepper, and 1 teaspoon of paprika. Add 1 pound of chicken and cook until browned. Pour in 2 cups of broth and simmer for 20 minutes.

Title: Taco Salad
Ingredients: Ground beef, lettuce, cheese, salsa, tortilla chips
Description: Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C). Grease a baking dish with 1 tablespoon of butter. In a bowl, mix 2 cups of flour, 1 teaspoon of baking powder, and 1/2 teaspoon of salt. In another bowl, whisk 1 cup of milk, 1 egg, and 1/2 cup of sugar. Combine wet and dry ingredients, pour into the baking dish, and bake for 25 minutes.

Title: Tom Yum Soup
Ingredients: Chicken, butter, cream, tomatoes, spices
Description: Heat 3 tablespoons of oil in a pan. Add 1 sliced bell pepper and 1 diced tomato. Cook for 5 minutes. Add 1 cup of chopped chicken, 1 teaspoon of cumin, and 1/2 teaspoon of chili powder. Stir well and cook for another 10 minutes.

Description: Heat 3 tablespoons of oil in a pan. Add 1 sliced bell pepper and 1 diced tomato. Cook for 5 minutes. Add 1 cup of chopped chicken, 1 teaspoon of cumin, and 1/2 teaspoon of chili powder. Stir well and cook for another 10 minutes.

Description: Chop 2 potatoes, 1 carrot, and 1 onion. Heat 2 tablespoons of oil in a pot. Sauté the onion for 3 minutes. Add the potatoes and carrots, followed by 4 cups of vegetable broth. Season with 1 teaspoon of salt and 1/2 teaspoon of thyme. Simmer for 20 minutes until tender.

Title: Sweet and Sour Chicken
Ingredients: Noodles, broth, pork, egg, green onions
Description: Chop 2 potatoes, 1 carrot, and 1 onion. Heat 2 tablespoons of oil in a pot. Sauté the onion for 3 minutes. Add the potatoes and carrots, followed by 4 cups of vegetable broth. Season with 1 teaspoon of salt and 1/2 teaspoon of thyme. Simmer for 20 minutes until tender.

Title: Taco Salad
Ingredients: Lentils, garlic, tomatoes, cumin, mustard seeds
Description: Heat a pan over medium heat. Add 2 tablespoons of oil. Sauté 1 chopped onion until golden. Add 2 cloves of minced garlic and cook for 1 minute. Stir in 1 teaspoon of salt, 1/2 teaspoon of pepper, and 1 teaspoon of paprika. Add 1 pound of chicken and cook until browned. Pour in 2 cups of broth and simmer for 20 minutes.

Title: Kung Pao Chicken
Ingredients: Dough, ground meat, onions, salt, pepper
Description: Boil 4 cups of water in a pot. Add 1 cup of rice and 1/2 teaspoon of salt. Cover and cook on low heat for 15 minutes. Fluff with a fork and serve.

Title: Croissant
Ingredients: Yam flour, water
Description: Chop 2 potatoes, 1 carrot, and 1 onion. Heat 2 tablespoons of oil in a pot. Sauté the onion for 3 minutes. Add the potatoes and carrots, followed by 4 cups of vegetable broth. Season with 1 teaspoon of salt and 1/2 teaspoon of thyme. Simmer for 20 minutes until tender.

Title: Green Curry
Ingredients: Beetroot, cabbage, potatoes, carrots, dill
Description: Marinate 1 pound of beef with 1 teaspoon of salt, 1/2 teaspoon of black pepper, and 1 tablespoon of soy sauce. Let it sit for 30 minutes. Heat a pan with 2 tablespoons of oil. Sear the beef for 5 minutes on each side. Reduce heat and cook for another 10 minutes, then serve.

Title: Butter Chicken
Ingredients: Flour, tomatoes, mozzarella, basil, olive oil
Description: Bring 6 cups of water to a boil. Add 2 cups of pasta and 1 teaspoon of salt. Cook for 10 minutes, then drain. In a saucepan, melt 2 tablespoons of butter, add 1/2 cup of cream, and 1/2 cup of grated cheese. Stir until smooth. Mix with the pasta and serve warm.

Title: Shakshuka

Title: Sweet and Sour Chicken

Ingredients: Chickpeas, tahini, lemon, garlic, olive oil

Description: Marinate 1 pound of beef with 1 teaspoon of salt, 1/2 teaspoon of black pepper, and 1 tablespoon of soy sauce. Let it sit for 30 minutes. Heat a pan with 2 tablespoons of oil. Sear the beef for 5 minutes on each side. Reduce heat and cook for another 10 minutes, then serve.

Title: Ratatouille
Ingredients: Tomatoes, eggs, onions, bell peppers, spices
Description: Chop 2 potatoes, 1 carrot, and 1 onion. Heat 2 tablespoons of oil in a pot. Sauté the onion for 3 minutes. Add the potatoes and carrots, followed by 4 cups of vegetable broth. Season with 1 teaspoon of salt and 1/2 teaspoon of thyme. Simmer for 20 minutes until tender.

Title: Pelmeni
Ingredients: Coconut milk, green curry paste, chicken, basil
Description: Bring 6 cups of water to a boil. Add 2 cups of pasta and 1 teaspoon of salt. Cook for 10 minutes, then drain. In a saucepan, melt 2 tablespoons of butter, add 1/2 cup of cream, and 1/2 cup of grated cheese. Stir until smooth. Mix with the pasta and serve warm.

Title: Pounded Yam
Ingredients: Eggplant, zucchini, bell peppers, tomatoes, herbs
Description: Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C). Grease a baking dish with 1 tablespoon of butter. In a bowl, mix 2 cups of flour, 1 teaspoon of baking powder, and 1/2 teaspoon of salt. In another bowl, whisk 1 cup of milk, 1 egg, and 1/2 cup of sugar. Combine wet and dry ingredients, pour into the baking dish, and bake for 25 minutes.

Title: Lasagna
Ingredients: Tortilla, beans, rice, cheese, chicken
Description: Boil 4 cups of water in a pot. Add 1 cup of rice and 1/2 teaspoon of salt. Cover and cook on low heat for 15 minutes. Fluff with a fork and serve.

Description: Boil 4 cups of water in a pot. Add 1 cup of rice and 1/2 teaspoon of salt. Cover and cook on low heat for 15 minutes. Fluff with a fork and serve.

Title: Borscht
Ingredients: Flour, butter, sugar, eggs, yeast
Description: Heat 3 tablespoons of oil in a pan. Add 1 sliced bell pepper and 1 diced tomato. Cook for 5 minutes. Add 1 cup of chopped chicken, 1 teaspoon of cumin, and 1/2 teaspoon of chili powder. Stir well and cook for another 10 minutes.

Title: Croissant
Ingredients: Egusi seeds, spinach, stockfish, palm oil
Description: Heat a pan over medium heat. Add 2 tablespoons of oil. Sauté 1 chopped onion until golden. Add 2 cloves of minced garlic and cook for 1 minute. Stir in 1 teaspoon of salt, 1/2 teaspoon of pepper, and 1 teaspoon of paprika. Add 1 pound of chicken and cook until browned. Pour in 2 cups of broth and simmer for 20 minutes.

Title: Taco Salad
Ingredients: Flour, butter, sugar, eggs, yeast
Description: Heat 3 tablespoons of oil in a pan. Add 1 sliced bell pepper and 1 diced tomato. Cook for 5 minutes. Add 1 cup of chopped chicken, 1 teaspoon of cumin, and 1/2 teaspoon of chili powder. Stir well and cook for another 10 minutes.

Title: Pelmeni
Ingredients: Shrimp, lemongrass, lime leaves, chili, broth
Description: Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C). Grease a baking dish with 1 tablespoon of butter. In a bowl, mix 2 cups of flour, 1 teaspoon of baking powder, and 1/2 teaspoon of salt. In another bowl, whisk 1 cup of milk, 1 egg, and 1/2 cup of sugar. Combine wet and dry ingredients, pour into the baking dish, and bake for 25 minutes.

Title: Burrito
Ingredients: Shrimp, flour, eggs, tempura sauce
Description: Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C). Grease a baking dish with 1 tablespoon of butter. In a bowl, mix 2 cups of flour, 1 teaspoon of baking powder, and 1/2 teaspoon of salt. In another bowl, whisk 1 cup of milk, 1 egg, and 1/2 cup of sugar. Combine wet and dry ingredients, pour into the baking dish, and bake for 25 minutes.

Title: Kung Pao Chicken
Ingredients: Noodles, broth, pork, egg, green onions
Description: Marinate 1 pound of beef with 1 teaspoon of salt, 1/2 teaspoon of black pepper, and 1 tablespoon of soy sauce. Let it sit for 30 minutes. Heat a pan with 2 tablespoons of oil. Sear the beef for 5 minutes on each side. Reduce heat and cook for another 10 minutes, then serve.

Title: Borscht

Title: Hummus
Ingredients: Coconut milk, green curry paste, chicken, basil
Description: In a blender, combine 2 bananas, 1 cup of milk, 1/2 teaspoon of cinnamon, and 1 tablespoon of honey. Blend until smooth. Serve chilled.

Title: Ratatouille

Description: Heat a pan over medium heat. Add 2 tablespoons of oil. Sauté 1 chopped onion until golden. Add 2 cloves of minced garlic and cook for 1 minute. Description: Heat 3 tablespoons of oil in a pan. Add 1 sliced bell pepper and 1 diced tomato. Cook for 5 minutes. Add 1 cup of chopped chicken, 1 teaspoon of cumin, and 1/2 teaspoon of chili powder. Stir well and cook for another 10 minutes.

Title: Tempura
Ingredients: Tortilla, beans, rice, cheese, chicken
Description: Boil 4 cups of water in a pot. Add 1 cup of rice and 1/2 teaspoon of salt. Cover and cook on low heat for 15 minutes. Fluff with a fork and serve.

Title: Ramen
Ingredients: Chickpeas, tahini, lemon, garlic, olive oil
Description: Chop 2 potatoes, 1 carrot, and 1 onion. Heat 2 tablespoons of oil in a pot. Sauté the onion for 3 minutes. Add the potatoes and carrots, followed by 4 cups of vegetable broth. Season with 1 teaspoon of salt and 1/2 teaspoon of thyme. Simmer for 20 minutes until tender.

Title: Ratatouille
Ingredients: Flour, tomatoes, mozzarella, basil, olive oil
Description: Marinate 1 pound of beef with 1 teaspoon of salt, 1/2 teaspoon of black pepper, and 1 tablespoon of soy sauce. Let it sit for 30 minutes. Heat a pan with 2 tablespoons of oil. Sear the beef for 5 minutes on each side. Reduce heat and cook for another 10 minutes, then serve.

Title: Lasagna
Ingredients: Lentils, garlic, tomatoes, cumin, mustard seeds
Description: Chop 2 potatoes, 1 carrot, and 1 onion. Heat 2 tablespoons of oil in a pot. Sauté the onion for 3 minutes. Add the potatoes and carrots, followed by 4 cups of vegetable broth. Season with 1 teaspoon of salt and 1/2 teaspoon of thyme. Simmer for 20 minutes until tender.

Title: Tom Yum Soup
Ingredients: Tortilla, beans, rice, cheese, chicken
Description: Heat a pan over medium heat. Add 2 tablespoons of oil. Sauté 1 chopped onion until golden. Add 2 cloves of minced garlic and cook for 1 minute. Stir in 1 teaspoon of salt, 1/2 teaspoon of pepper, and 1 teaspoon of paprika. Add 1 pound of chicken and cook until browned. Pour in 2 cups of broth and simmer for 20 minutes.

Title: Taco Salad
Ingredients: Egusi seeds, spinach, stockfish, palm oil
Description: In a blender, combine 2 bananas, 1 cup of milk, 1/2 teaspoon of cinnamon, and 1 tablespoon of honey. Blend until smooth. Serve chilled.

Title: Hummus
Ingredients: Dough, ground meat, onions, salt, pepper
Description: Chop 2 potatoes, 1 carrot, and 1 onion. Heat 2 tablespoons of oil in a pot. Sauté the onion for 3 minutes. Add the potatoes and carrots, followed by 4 cups of vegetable broth. Season with 1 teaspoon of salt and 1/2 teaspoon of thyme. Simmer for 20 minutes until tender.

Title: Kung Pao Chicken

Description: In a blender, combine 2 bananas, 1 cup of milk, 1/2 teaspoon of cinnamon, and 1 tablespoon of honey. Blend until smooth. Serve chilled.

Description: Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C). Grease a baking dish with 1 tablespoon of butter. In a bowl, mix 2 cups of flour, 1 teaspoon of baking powder, and 1/2 teaspoon of salt. In another bowl, whisk 1 cup of milk, 1 egg, and 1/2 cup of sugar. Combine wet and dry ingredients, pour into the baking dish, and bake for 25 minutes.

Title: Pelmeni
Ingredients: Lentils, garlic, tomatoes, cumin, mustard seeds
Description: Marinate 1 pound of beef with 1 teaspoon of salt, 1/2 teaspoon of black pepper, and 1 tablespoon of soy sauce. Let it sit for 30 minutes. Heat a pan with 2 tablespoons of oil. Sear the beef for 5 minutes on each side. Reduce heat and cook for another 10 minutes, then serve.

Title: Pizza Margherita

Description: Marinate 1 pound of beef with 1 teaspoon of salt, 1/2 teaspoon of black pepper, and 1 tablespoon of soy sauce. Let it sit for 30 minutes. Heat a pan with 2 tablespoons of oil. Sear the beef for 5 minutes on each side. Reduce heat and cook for another 10 minutes, then serve.

Title: Sweet and Sour Chicken
Ingredients: Yam flour, water
Description: Heat a pan over medium heat. Add 2 tablespoons of oil. Sauté 1 chopped onion until golden. Add 2 cloves of minced garlic and cook for 1 minute. Stir in 1 teaspoon of salt, 1/2 teaspoon of pepper, and 1 teaspoon of paprika. Add 1 pound of chicken and cook until browned. Pour in 2 cups of broth and simmer for 20 minutes.

Description: Boil 4 cups of water in a pot. Add 1 cup of rice and 1/2 teaspoon of salt. Cover and cook on low heat for 15 minutes. Fluff with a fork and serve.

Title: Borscht
Ingredients: Flour, tomatoes, mozzarella, basil, olive oil
Description: Bring 6 cups of water to a boil. Add 2 cups of pasta and 1 teaspoon of salt. Cook for 10 minutes, then drain. In a saucepan, melt 2 tablespoons of butter, add 1/2 cup of cream, and 1/2 cup of grated cheese. Stir until smooth. Mix with the pasta and serve warm.

Title: Egusi Soup

Title: Burrito
Ingredients: Tomatoes, eggs, onions, bell peppers, spices
Description: In a blender, combine 2 bananas, 1 cup of milk, 1/2 teaspoon of cinnamon, and 1 tablespoon of honey. Blend until smooth. Serve chilled.

Title: Tom Yum Soup

Description: Chop 2 potatoes, 1 carrot, and 1 onion. Heat 2 tablespoons of oil in a pot. Sauté the onion for 3 minutes. Add the potatoes and carrots, followed by 4 cups of vegetable broth. Season with 1 teaspoon of salt and 1/2 teaspoon of thyme. Simmer for 20 minutes until tender.

Description: Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C). Grease a baking dish with 1 tablespoon of butter. In a bowl, mix 2 cups of flour, 1 teaspoon of baking powder, and 1/2 teaspoon of salt. In another bowl, whisk 1 cup of milk, 1 egg, and 1/2 cup of sugar. Combine wet and dry ingredients, pour into the baking dish, and bake for 25 minutes.

Title: Pizza Margherita
Ingredients: Egusi seeds, spinach, stockfish, palm oil
Description: Boil 4 cups of water in a pot. Add 1 cup of rice and 1/2 teaspoon of salt. Cover and cook on low heat for 15 minutes. Fluff with a fork and serve.

Title: Pizza Margherita
Ingredients: Lentils, garlic, tomatoes, cumin, mustard seeds
Description: Marinate 1 pound of beef with 1 teaspoon of salt, 1/2 teaspoon of black pepper, and 1 tablespoon of soy sauce. Let it sit for 30 minutes. Heat a pan with 2 tablespoons of oil. Sear the beef for 5 minutes on each side. Reduce heat and cook for another 10 minutes, then serve.

Title: Tom Yum Soup
Ingredients: Lentils, garlic, tomatoes, cumin, mustard seeds
Description: Heat 3 tablespoons of oil in a pan. Add 1 sliced bell pepper and 1 diced tomato. Cook for 5 minutes. Add 1 cup of chopped chicken, 1 teaspoon of cumin, and 1/2 teaspoon of chili powder. Stir well and cook for another 10 minutes.

Title: Sweet and Sour Chicken
Ingredients: Yam flour, water
Description: In a blender, combine 2 bananas, 1 cup of milk, 1/2 teaspoon of cinnamon, and 1 tablespoon of honey. Blend until smooth. Serve chilled.

Title: Dal Tadka
Ingredients: Chickpeas, tahini, lemon, garlic, olive oil
Description: Marinate 1 pound of beef with 1 teaspoon of salt, 1/2 teaspoon of black pepper, and 1 tablespoon of soy sauce. Let it sit for 30 minutes. Heat a pan with 2 tablespoons of oil. Sear the beef for 5 minutes on each side. Reduce heat and cook for another 10 minutes, then serve.

Title: Shakshuka
Ingredients: Coconut milk, green curry paste, chicken, basil
Description: Bring 6 cups of water to a boil. Add 2 cups of pasta and 1 teaspoon of salt. Cook for 10 minutes, then drain. In a saucepan, melt 2 tablespoons of butter, add 1/2 cup of cream, and 1/2 cup of grated cheese. Stir until smooth. Mix with the pasta and serve warm.

Title: Taco Salad
Ingredients: Flour, butter, sugar, eggs, yeast

Description: Bring 6 cups of water to a boil. Add 2 cups of pasta and 1 teaspoon of salt. Cook for 10 minutes, then drain. In a saucepan, melt 2 tablespoons of butter, add 1/2 cup of cream, and 1/2 cup of grated cheese. Stir until smooth. Mix with the pasta and serve warm.

Title: Tom Yum Soup
Ingredients: Noodles, broth, pork, egg, green onions
Description: Heat a pan over medium heat. Add 2 tablespoons of oil. Sauté 1 chopped onion until golden. Add 2 cloves of minced garlic and cook for 1 minute. Stir in 1 teaspoon of salt, 1/2 teaspoon of pepper, and 1 teaspoon of paprika. Add 1 pound of chicken and cook until browned. Pour in 2 cups of broth and simmer for 20 minutes.

Title: Taco Salad
Ingredients: Tortilla, beans, rice, cheese, chicken
Description: Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C). Grease a baking dish with 1 tablespoon of butter. In a bowl, mix 2 cups of flour, 1 teaspoon of baking powder, and 1/2 teaspoon of salt. In another bowl, whisk 1 cup of milk, 1 egg, and 1/2 cup of sugar. Combine wet and dry ingredients, pour into the baking dish, and bake for 25 minutes.

Title: Egusi Soup
Ingredients: Pasta, tomato sauce, cheese, ground beef, basil
Description: In a blender, combine 2 bananas, 1 cup of milk, 1/2 teaspoon of cinnamon, and 1 tablespoon of honey. Blend until smooth. Serve chilled.

Description: Bring 6 cups of water to a boil. Add 2 cups of pasta and 1 teaspoon of salt. Cook for 10 minutes, then drain. In a saucepan, melt 2 tablespoons of butter, add 1/2 cup of cream, and 1/2 cup of grated cheese. Stir until smooth. Mix with the pasta and serve warm.

Title: Sweet and Sour Chicken
Ingredients: Coconut milk, green curry paste, chicken, basil
Description: Chop 2 potatoes, 1 carrot, and 1 onion. Heat 2 tablespoons of oil in a pot. Sauté the onion for 3 minutes. Add the potatoes and carrots, followed by 4 cups of vegetable broth. Season with 1 teaspoon of salt and 1/2 teaspoon of thyme. Simmer for 20 minutes until tender.

Title: Sweet and Sour Chicken
Ingredients: Pasta, tomato sauce, cheese, ground beef, basil
Description: Heat a pan over medium heat. Add 2 tablespoons of oil. Sauté 1 chopped onion until golden. Add 2 cloves of minced garlic and cook for 1 minute. Stir in 1 teaspoon of salt, 1/2 teaspoon of pepper, and 1 teaspoon of paprika. Add 1 pound of chicken and cook until browned. Pour in 2 cups of broth and simmer for 20 minutes.

Title: Croissant
Ingredients: Lentils, garlic, tomatoes, cumin, mustard seeds
Description: Heat a pan over medium heat. Add 2 tablespoons of oil. Sauté 1 chopped onion until golden. Add 2 cloves of minced garlic and cook for 1 minute. Title: Pizza Margherita
Ingredients: Chicken, bell peppers, pineapple, soy sauce
Description: Marinate 1 pound of beef with 1 teaspoon of salt, 1/2 teaspoon of black pepper, and 1 tablespoon of soy sauce. Let it sit for 30 minutes. Heat a pan with 2 tablespoons of oil. Sear the beef for 5 minutes on each side. Reduce heat and cook for another 10 minutes, then serve.

Ingredients: Coconut milk, green curry paste, chicken, basil
Description: Boil 4 cups of water in a pot. Add 1 cup of rice and 1/2 teaspoon of salt. Cover and cook on low heat for 15 minutes. Fluff with a fork and serve.

Title: Sweet and Sour Chicken
Ingredients: Flour, tomatoes, mozzarella, basil, olive oil
Description: Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C). Grease a baking dish with 1 tablespoon of butter. In a bowl, mix 2 cups of flour, 1 teaspoon of baking powder, and 1/2 teaspoon of salt. In another bowl, whisk 1 cup of milk, 1 egg, and 1/2 cup of sugar. Combine wet and dry ingredients, pour into the baking dish, and bake for 25 minutes.

Title: Taco Salad
Ingredients: Shrimp, lemongrass, lime leaves, chili, broth
Description: Heat a pan over medium heat. Add 2 tablespoons of oil. Sauté 1 chopped onion until golden. Add 2 cloves of minced garlic and cook for 1 minute. Stir in 1 teaspoon of salt, 1/2 teaspoon of pepper, and 1 teaspoon of paprika. Add 1 pound of chicken and cook until browned. Pour in 2 cups of broth and simmer for 20 minutes.

Title: Tempura
Ingredients: Chicken, peanuts, chili peppers, soy sauce
Description: Marinate 1 pound of beef with 1 teaspoon of salt, 1/2 teaspoon of black pepper, and 1 tablespoon of soy sauce. Let it sit for 30 minutes. Heat a pan with 2 tablespoons of oil. Sear the beef for 5 minutes on each side. Reduce heat and cook for another 10 minutes, then serve.

Title: Lasagna
Ingredients: Pasta, tomato sauce, cheese, ground beef, basil
Description: Marinate 1 pound of beef with 1 teaspoon of salt, 1/2 teaspoon of black pepper, and 1 tablespoon of soy sauce. Let it sit for 30 minutes. Heat a pan with 2 tablespoons of oil. Sear the beef for 5 minutes on each side. Reduce heat and cook for another 10 minutes, then serve.

Title: Kung Pao Chicken
Ingredients: Ground beef, lettuce, cheese, salsa, tortilla chips
Description: Marinate 1 pound of beef with 1 teaspoon of salt, 1/2 teaspoon of black pepper, and 1 tablespoon of soy sauce. Let it sit for 30 minutes. Heat a pan with 2 tablespoons of oil. Sear the beef for 5 minutes on each side. Reduce heat and cook for another 10 minutes, then serve.

Title: Butter Chicken
Ingredients: Lentils, garlic, tomatoes, cumin, mustard seeds
Description: Heat 3 tablespoons of oil in a pan. Add 1 sliced bell pepper and 1 diced tomato. Cook for 5 minutes. Add 1 cup of chopped chicken, 1 teaspoon of cumin, and 1/2 teaspoon of chili powder. Stir well and cook for another 10 minutes.
